{{ tffile "examples/data-sources/thousandeyes_dashboard_filter/data-source.tf" }}

## Using `filter_id` with dashboards

- Pass `filter_id` to [`thousandeyes_dashboard.global_filter_id`](../resources/dashboard.md) to set the dashboard's saved default filter.
- Saved dashboard filters are dashboard-wide filter sets created in the ThousandEyes UI or API. They are not the same as widget-level `filter` blocks, `number_cards.filter`, or `multi_metric_columns.filter`.
- Use widget-level filters when you want to pin a specific widget or column to a set of IDs. Use `global_filter_id` when you want the dashboard to open with a reusable saved filter set.

